    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The only reliable record of the occasion is given by Paul himself, in his second letter to Timothy. &ldquo;At my first answer,&rdquo; the apostle wrote, &ldquo;no man stood with me, but all men forsook me: I pray God that it may not be laid to their charge. Notwithstanding the Lord stood with me, and strengthened me; that by me the preaching might be fully known, and that all the Gentiles might hear: and I was delivered out of the mouth of the lion.&rdquo; <span class=\"egwlink egwlink_bible\" title=\"2 Timothy 4:16\" data-link=\"1965.60959\">2 Timothy 4:16, 17</span>.",
