    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Thus pleads the advocate of truth. Faithful among the faithless, loyal among the disloyal, he stands as God&apos;s representative, and his voice is as a voice from heaven. There is no fear, no sadness, no discouragement in word or look. Strong in a consciousness of innocence, clothed in the panoply of truth, he rejoices that he is a son of God. His words are as a shout of victory above the roar of battle. He declares the cause to which he has devoted his life, to be the only cause that can never fail. Though he may perish, the gospel will not perish. God lives, and His truth will triumph.",
